content: The hotel is situated on strategic location. However, my experience in this hotel was very disappointing. The room was dusty and the carpet, bed linen, and towels are full of hair. The room service menu is limited and the quality of food was below average. At Your Service, the guest service center where you should inquire and place orders for housekeeping and in room dining, was not available most of the time, you have to dial the number for several times until someone picks up the phone, I've tried it in different timing and the result is almost the same every time. On the other hand, the team members that I have encountered with were in general polite, supportive, and friendly with minor exceptions. I guess, the hotel's management must go back to the basics in hospitality, and ensure that the rooms are clean, food quality is good, and service team is available to answer the phone. By the way, in my second week, I have received a call from the guest relations asking about my feedback about the hotel, and I've reported everything, but nothing has really changed, though, my stay at the hotel was a lengthy one and I had no other choice but to stay there for the whole period.

content: MoreIt's was my first time during this Covid time. The arrangements were superb. Not very crowdy. Very systematic approach. You have to have a bus ticket, park your car at Kudai parking and get into the tent. Show your permit and they will give you a ticket to get in the bus. . Bus will take you to the Haram, it will dropped you off around 700 to 800 meters aways from Haram. Then you have to walk. Upon reaching at your authorized door guard will check your permit and let you through. Thermal cameras are installed for covid scanning. The way will take you straight to mataf. Mataf area is marked by various colors of tapes. Very convenient and easy to perform. After mataf pray two rakat sunnah and move to safa and marwa. Upon completion of Saii you will return back to your entrance door and move back to kudai bus station. Barber shops are open in clock tower building. Keep your Ticket with you. As it requires to show when you ride back. Bus then will take you back to kudai parking.

The Jawathi, Gotha, or Juatha Mosque is located in Al-Ahsa Governorate, in eastern Saudi Arabia, and the mosque, which is located within a park known by the same name, is about 17 kilometers northeast of Al-Hofuf. This mosque was built during the era of the Prophet Muhammad, peace be upon him, and the inhabitants of the country of Bahrain, Banu Abd Qais, who were the ones who initiated their conversion to Islam willingly, not by compulsion, and the Prophet praised the people of these lands by saying (Honor your brothers, for they are like you people who converted to Islam voluntarily and not involuntarily), and the rules of this mosque are still List to our current time Its origin is from the corpses of the man, if he panics, it is as if they would return to it when they were terrified, they called it that. This is supported by the presence of a fortress on the site, and the site of Jawahi now, a site of sand dunes, and it has depressions in which evidence of old settlement and buildings are broken. Active settlement in the location of the cumulative hills within the scope of the sand reservation project, the National Park in Al-Ahsa, where there are groups of archaeological hills covered by sand and spread over them many varieties of pottery and ceramic fragments and types of colored and white transparent glass The mosque is characterized by a unique architectural style, and it was built from jar and clay mortar, and its roof is made of sandalwood and has a total area of ​​about 206.5 m and accommodates about 170 worshipers, and the mosque consists of a prayer house containing three corridors, and the mosque also contains a share for bullying, and a room used as a warehouse, The mosque contains three towers that are placed on the outer pillars of the mosque (Original) مغلق حاليا . مسجد جواثى أو جوثا أو جواثا، يقع في محافظة الأحساء شرق المملكة العربية السعودية، ويبعد المسجد الذي يقع ضمن متنزه يعرف بالاسم نفسه، نحو 17 كيلومتراً شمال شرق مدينة الهفوف. بني هذا المسجد في عهد النبي محمد عليه السلام وتشرف ببنائه سكان بلاد إقليم البحرين بنو عبد قيس وهم الذين بادروا بإسلامهم طوعاً لا كرهاً وقد مدح النبي أهل هذه الديار بقوله (أكرموا أخوانكم فإنهم أشبه الناس بكم أسلموا طوعاً لا كرهاً)، ولا تزال قواعد هذا المسجد قائمة إلى وقتنا الحالي جواثى أصله من جأث الرجل إذا فزع فكأنهم لما كانوا يرجعون إليها عند الفزع سموها بذلك وهذا يؤيده وجود حصن بالموقع وموقع جواثى الآن موقع كثبان رملية، وبه منخفضات تظهر فيها دلائل استيطان قديم ومبان مندثرة، ربما تكون بقايا جواثى الأمس أو جزءا منها، وتظهر بالموقع دلائل استقرار نشط في موضع التلال التراكمية ضمن نطاق مشروع حجز الرمال المنتزه الوطني بالأحساء، فتوجد بالموقع مجموعات من التلال الأثرية التي تغطيها الرمال وتنتشر فوقها أصناف عديدة من الكسر الفخارية والخزفية وأنواع من الزجاج الملون والأبيض الشفاف يتميز المسجد بطراز معماري فريد، وقد تم بناؤه من ال جر ومونة الطين، وسقفه من خشب السندل وتبلغ مساحته الكلية نحو 206.5م ويتسع لنحو 170مصلياً، ويتكون المسجد من بيت الصلاة يحتوي على ثلاث أروقة ، كما يحتوي المسجد على حصة للتنمر، وغرفة
